- make sure repeated components are made reusable and  called where needed
- Build like a senior engineer: maintain clean architecture, modularity and clear separation of concerns always.

- Folder & File structure discipline is a HIGH PRIORITY requirement.

- Never rebuild a component that has already been built unless I explicitly request a refactor or modification.

- Never invent new colors, typography, spacings, utils, or naming tokens outside what we have already defined.

- If a token is missing → ask before generating new ones.

Design System Rules

- All colors MUST come from /src/design/colors.ts

- All typography tokens MUST come from /src/design/typography.ts

- All spacing / utils MUST come from /src/design/utils.ts

- If new tokens are needed → create proposed tokens inside these files FIRST, get approval, then use them.

Code Style Requirements

- Functional components, hooks-only (no class components)

- Typescript ALWAYS

- Clean naming, no abbreviation confusion (prefer clarity > shortness)

- Avoid deeply nested code. Always refactor to smaller composable parts.

- Use readability + maintainability as top priority.

General AI Building Enforcement

-Before generating new complex screens → always reason about file placement first.

- If a file or component already exists → modify in place, do NOT recreate duplicates.

-Ask clarifying questions if architecture decisions are ambiguous.

- Treat structure + maintainability as the highest priority constraint.

- Make sure whatever you build is responsive to both mobile and desktop devices.
- Make sure to always get icon from the design file  that is tagged.
